SIMPLE: indigenous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indigenous
<hw>In*dig"e*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indigenus</ets>, <ets>indigena</ets>, fr. OL. <ets>indu</ets> (fr.
<ets>in</ets> in) + the root of L. <ets>gignere</ets> to beget, bear.
See <er>In</er>, and <er>Gender</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Native; produced, growing, or living, naturally in a
country or climate; not exotic; not imported.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Negroes were all transported from Africa and are not
<qex>indigenous</qex> or proper natives of America.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In America, cotton, being <qex>indigenous</qex>, is cheap.</q>
<rj><qau>Lion Playas.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Native; inherent; innate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Joy and hope are emotions <qex>indigenous</qex> to the human
mind.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indigent</ent>⟦br⟧
